Title: Floating Autonomous Reforestation Platforms: Restoring Coastal Ecosystems at Scale
Sections:
	•	Abstract: Solar-powered autonomous barges planting mangroves, kelp, and shoreline vegetation.
	•	Problem Statement: Coastal erosion, habitat loss, climate resilience.
	•	Proposed Solution: Self-navigating, AI-guided drone platforms integrated with floating monitoring and compute nodes.
	•	Technical Design: Energy system, navigation, planting mechanisms, environmental monitoring.
	•	Deployment & Testing: Coastal pilot zones, autonomous operation, ecological monitoring.
	•	Use Cases: Ecosystem restoration, climate resilience, scientific research.
	•	Impact & Scalability: Rapid deployment in multiple geographies, minimal human labor, integrated environmental data.
	•	Future Research & Partnerships: NGOs, climate initiatives, marine research institutes.
